what are the first symptoms of lung cancer early lung cancer often does not cause symptoms but as the cancer grows common symptoms may include a cough that gets worse or does not go away breathing trouble such as shortness of breath constant chest pain coughing up blood a hoarse voice frequent lung infections such as pneumonia feeling very tired all the time weight loss with no known cause Lung cancer Pneumonia Prostate cancer Pulmonary embolism Cancer Gastroesophageal reflux disease Stomach cancer Aspergillosis Traumatic brain injury Asthma Chlamydophila pneumoniae Esophageal cancer Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Group A streptococcal infection Cystic fibrosis Aspartame Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Tuberculosis Coeliac disease Colorectal cancer Urinary incontinence Medicine Asbestosis Tobacco smoking Breast cancer Ovarian cancer Drowning Pneumothorax Shock Blastomycosis Cancer of the larynx Histoplasmosis Human adaptation to space Mesothelioma Panic attack First aid Pancreatic cancer Acute lymphoblastic leukemia Hip fracture Pneumocystis jiroveci pneumonia Sarcoidosis Acute respiratory distress syndrome Lung Duchenne muscular dystrophy Pulmonary alveolus Endometriosis Heartworm Autoimmune diseases Breastfeeding Diabetic neuropathy Pleural cavity Metastasis Atrial septal defect Leukemia Hodgkin's lymphoma Poliomyelitis Intravenous therapy Diarrhea Multiple sclerosis Bronchiolitis Myelodysplastic syndrome Rheumatoid arthritis Pulmonology Exercise Narcotic Cannabis (drug) Pulmonary edema Cervical cancer Chronic fatigue syndrome AIDS Black Death Stroke Myasthenia gravis Goodpasture's syndrome Tocopherol Muscle Hyperventilation Pertussis Common misconceptions about HIV and AIDS Beryllium Decompression sickness Anemia Diabetes mellitus Marfan syndrome Bacterial pneumonia Endometrial cancer Kaposi's sarcoma Cocaine Air embolism Infectious mononucleosis Chest pain Viral pneumonia Peptic ulcer Bubonic plague Diffuse parenchymal lung disease 